    Scope and Contents
Deck discusses her experiences as a young women during WWII on the homefront in St. Louis: marrying a soldier, home life, rationing, coping with the absence of her husband, and children. Also mentions St. Louis before the war, high school, and attending Monticello College in Godfrey, Illinois. 1 tape, 45 mins., 17 pp. 
Interview by Jeffrey A. Eldred, 1993 
